+    You can set ``reverse`` to ``True`` to sort the groups in descending
+    order.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items in users|groupby("city", reverse=True) %}
+          <li>{{ city }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    You can pass a ``key_transform`` callable to change how the group
+    key is displayed without affecting how items are grouped.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for month, items in users|groupby("signup_date.month", key_transform=month_name) %}
+          <li>{{ month }}: {{ items|map(attribute="name")|join(", ") }}</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``reverse`` and ``key_transform`` parameters.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
